curatedMetagenomicDataCuration.Rmd

Abstract

This vignette checks every file under inst/curated that ends in _metadata.tsv against the template file inst/extdata/template.csv, and shows problems found. Two types of errors can appear: 1) A “column name error” means a column name is not found at all in template.csv. 2) An “entry error” means at least one value in a column does not match the rules defined for that column. This script will list the illegal values next to the row name they were found in. Entries are checked against the following rules: a) uniqueness - if “non-unique”, then duplicate are allowed in the column, if “unique”, then each duplicated value is an error and will be listed. b) requiredness - if “optional” then NA values are allowed, if “required” then any NA value is an error. c) multiplevalues - if TRUE, then multiple semicolon-separated are allowed in a single cell, if FALSE, no semicolon is allowed. d) allowedvalues is a regular expression definining legal values. These are assumed to be POSIX 1003.2 extended regular expressions (see ?grep). Finally, the template file contains a free-form “description” field explaining what that column should contain, sometimes including units of measurement. The source repository for this document is https://github.com/waldronlab/curatedMetagenomicDataCuration.

This vignette was built on 2021-04-29 14:35:58 based on curatedMetagenomicDataCuration version 0.99.6.
